  "text": "In intestinal tissues, the intracellular localization of GLUT8 was also proved by immunohistochemistry studies showing a supranuclear distribution next to the apical membrane [CITATION_1] . The investigation of the physiological role of GLUT8 in hexose uptake revealed that GLUT8 was an intracellular transporter that suppressed fructose uptake through the enterocytes. This study demonstrated that GLUT8-deficient mice exhibited increased enterocyte fructose absorption and increased serum fructose concentrations after oral fructose administration [CITATION_2] . GLUT8 was also regulating the levels and trafficking of GLUT12.",
